items.title: Road to the Postseason: Sept. 17
items.summary: The Astros could be celebrating right alongside the Indians as their magic number to clinch the AL West dropped to one, and the Dodgers topped the Nationals for their fourth straight win to keep a handle on the best record in baseball.
items.content: The Astros could be celebrating right alongside the Indians as their magic number to clinch the AL West dropped to one, and the Dodgers topped the Nationals for their fourth straight win to keep a handle on the best record in baseball.

items.title: Leader Watch: Greinke bolsters Cy Young bid
items.summary: Zack Greinke continues to lead the D-backs' march to the postseason, and his return to steady dominance in 2017 might make him a National League Cy Young Award favorite by the time all's said and done.
items.content: Zack Greinke continues to lead the D-backs' march to the postseason, and his return to steady dominance in 2017 might make him a National League Cy Young Award favorite by the time all's said and done.

items.title: Upton homers twice, sets career high in RBIs
items.summary: Justin Upton delivered precisely the type of offensive performance the Angels envisioned when they acquired him from the Tigers two weeks ago, homering twice in a 2-0 win over the Rangers on Saturday night at Angel Stadium.
items.content: Justin Upton delivered precisely the type of offensive performance the Angels envisioned when they acquired him from the Tigers two weeks ago, homering twice in a 2-0 win over the Rangers on Saturday night at Angel Stadium.

items.title: Banged-up Beltre determined to keep battling
items.summary: Adrian Beltre has now played in four straight games while dealing with a strained left hamstring muscle. He has been limited to designated hitter duty and there is a chance he could aggravate it, but he doesn't care.
